{{Infobox Minor League Baseball | name = DSL Dodgers | founded = 1989 | city = Dominican Republic | misc = | logo = | uniformlogo = | class level = Rookie | past class level = | current league = [[Dominican Summer League]] | conference = | division = Boca Chica Northwest | past league = | majorleague = [[Los Angeles Dodgers]] | pastmajorleague = | nickname = DSL Dodgers | pastnames = {{plainlist| *DSL Dodgers 1 *DSL Dodgers 2 *DSL Cibao Dodgers *DSL San Pedro de Macoris Dodgers }} | ballpark = Las Palmas Complex | pastparks = | leaguenum = 8 | leaguechamps = {{hlist|1988|1989|1992|1993|1996|1997|2000|2017}} | divnum = 0 | divisionchamps = | owner = Los Angeles Dodgers | manager = [[Austin Chubb]] | gm = }}
The '''Dominican Summer Dodgers''' are a [[minor league baseball]] team in the [[Dominican Summer League]]. The team plays in the Boca Chica Northwest division and is affiliated with the [[Los Angeles Dodgers]].
They have operated since 1989. Occasionally the Dodgers have fielded two teams in the DSL. In 1990, they had the DSL Cibao Dodgers and the DSL San Pedro de Macoris Dodgers and from 1992&ndash;2004 they had the DSL Dodgers 1 and DSL Dodgers 2.
