{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}
The '''Hankiralli''' is a [[Finland|Finnish]] motor [[Rallying|rally]], in the [[Europe]]an Championship. In 1981, Finnish driver [[Ulf Grönholm]] was killed in practice for this event. His son, [[Marcus Grönholm]], later went on to become the 2000 and 2002 World Champion rally driver. [[Sweden|Swedish]] driver [[Stig Blomqvist]] won the event twice, in 1971 and 1977, in a [[Saab 96]] V4.



